-- Copper Jumps to Record in London, 2-Year High in New York on Currency Risk
-- B y   J a m e s   P o o l e
-- 2010-12-07T08:03:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-07/copper-jumps-to-record-in-london-2-year-high-in-new-york-on-currency-risk.html
Copper climbed to a record $8,970 a
metric ton in London on concern that government moves to pump
money into the global economy may weaken currencies, boosting
demand for commodities as a hedge.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
